path.pcbmode:text: Board details: Name: powerBoard? Revision: first Description: Putting some ideas down. A battery replacement board that can be powered from various sources. License: CERN Open Hardware Licence v1.2 Design by: Kyle Jarvis

Manufacturing: RoHS and lead free compliant manufacturing process Unit of length: Millimetre (mm) Number of layers: 2 ('top', 'bottom') Board thickness: 1.6 mm Material: FR4 35/35 um copper Silkscreen: top and bottom, white Soldermask: top and bottom, blue Surface finish: lead-free
* Do not add marking/logos without Boldport's authorisation * Remove silkscreen from pads unless specified otherwise * Boldport must approve plots before production
